Commentary.Commentary: We are back for the second session of play here. The Bangladesh players make their way out into the middle now. The openers for Pakistan, Abdullah Shafique and Abid Ali follow them out too. Abu Jayed to begin with the ball for the hosts. Here he comes...
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

The surface still looks good for batting as it hasn't changed much but Bangladesh bowlers will look to do what Pakistan bowlers did today and would try to keep them on the back foot. An interesting session coming up. Do join us for the second session shortly.

Opting to bat first, Bangladesh had a nervy start as none of the top 4 could get going and were reeling at 49-4. Things changed for them then as Liton Das and Mushfiqur Rahim joined hands and fought back showing great resilience and ended Day 1 without any more hiccups where Liton Das also brought up his maiden ton. They were unscathed on Day 1 and the overnight batters would have looked to continue for long but that wasn't the case to be as Liton Das departed early after a good knock of 114. The debutant, Yasir Ali too couldn't survive for long. Mushfiqur Rahim looked well on his course for a century but got out. Taijul Islam and Mehidy Hasan scored some handy runs and brought up the 300 for Bangladesh. While the former departed, Mehidy Hasan kept playing but ran out of partners from the other end. Only 77 runs added to the overnight total but Bangladesh would be still happy with their efforts given the kind of start they had.

Pakistan bowlers were right up top on Day 1 at the start as they rattled the top order in pretty quick succession to keep Bangladesh on the back foot. However, they couldn't capitalize after that and the pitch got only better to bat on which meant that the bowlers did not get any purchase and after having the first session to themselves, they toiled and did not manage to get any wicket post the first session on Day 1. On Day 2, the new ball worked pretty well for them and they would have hoped for early inroads and got exactly that as Hasan Ali first scalped the well set Liton Das and broke the 206-run stand between him and Mushfiqur Rahim. After that, he showed no remorse to the debutant Yasir Ali and knocked him over with a peach. Faheem Ashraf got the better of Mushfiqur Rahim but they were troubled a little by the lower order but Hasan Ali ensured that Bangladesh do not get past 350 and ended the innings with a five-fer.

Hasan Ali ends with a five-fer and ensured that Bangladesh tailenders does not score much. Bangladesh have been bundled out for 330 and Pakistan will be happy with that after a scary-looking partnership between Mushfiqur Rahim and Liton Das.

OUT! BOWLED 'EM! Hasan Ali grabs two-in-two and ends with a 5-fer! He has bowled supremely well today and he will be very happy to end Bangladesh's innings. Around off, on a length, the ball lands and shapes in slightly, Ebadot Hossain looks to defend but misses and the wickets behind take a beating. BANGLADESH END ON 330!
Ebadot Hossain is the last batsman to walk in.

Mushfiqur Rahim straightaway goes for a review for caught behind. There was a clear sound of something. It's a fair delivery. UltraEdge shows there is a spike as the ball passes the bat. The on-field decision stays and Bangladesh lose a review.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Mushfiqur Rahim has to go back for 91 and the review does not save him. Ashraf serves this on a length, in the fourth stump channel, Rahim looks to defend this close to his body, but it seems like he has nicked this, as the ball goes to Rizwan, who collects and appeals and the finger goes up. Rahim goes for the review straightaway, but there was a loud sound as the ball passed the bat, so it is surprising that he has taken this. UltraEdge rolls in and there is a clear spike as the ball passes the bat. At the same time though, the lower part of Mushfiqur Rahim's bat also looks to be brushing his pad. The umpire sticks with his original decision but Rahim feels as though the noise was off his bat touching his pad. Nevertheless, he has to go back and his brilliant knock comes to an end.
Commentary.Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Faheem Ashraf

We are ready for the action on Day 2! Pakistan players stride out to the middle. The overnight batters Mushfiqur Rahim and Liton Das make their way to the middle as well. Surprisingly, Pakistan start with spin. Nauman Ali to start with the ball.

The overnight batters for the Bangla Tigers will look to continue their good work and help the hosts post a big total on board. Das has already got his hundred whereas Rahim is getting closer to his ton too. If these two can bat out one or two more sessions, then Pakistan will be under more pressure. The visitors have the new cherry to use to destroy this stand and then take a couple more wickets after that. Shaheen Afridi and Hasan Ali were in good touch early in the first session on Day 1 and if they can replicate the same, then Pakistan can really dominate proceedings. It should be an interesting day of cricket. Stay tuned as we bring you more updates.

Hello and a warm welcome to the coverage of Day 2 of the first Test between Pakistan and Bangladesh. The first day proved to be a fruitful one for the hosts as they ended the day on 253/4 after they were in a position where they were placed at 49/4. This was all due to the good work by the duo of Liton Das and Mushfiqur Rahim as they have stitched a stand of 204 runs, which included a maiden ton from Das and a handy knock from Rahim too. Let's see what's in store for us today...
... DAY 2, SESSION 1 ...

Right then. That is all we have from Day 1. Bangladesh will be looking to continue their good work, whereas, Pakistan will be hoping to break this stand as soon as possible. The action on Day 2 will begin at 10 am local (4 am GMT). Do join us then. Ciao!

Pakistan started the game off in top fashion but have been on the back foot in the second and third sessions of the Day. In the first session, their new-ball bowlers were on fire, especially, Shaheen Afridi, who was making life tough for the Bangla batters. Apart from Nauman Ali, all of their bowlers got a wicket in the first session and it looked like the same trend would continue, but alas, it was not meant to be for the visitors as Rahim and Das went about their business nicely. After the initial burst, the pitch too did not offer a lot of support to the bowlers or spinners and they failed to grab a wicket in the last two sessions. A hard day at work for them and they would look to get some rest and come out on Day 2 to hunt a few more wickets quickly.

Bangladesh got off to a horrible start as both their openers went back in quick succession. Najmul Hossain Shanto and Mominul Haque looked to steady things but they too made their way back to the shed, as the hosts slipped from 47/2 to 49/4. The onus fell on the duo of Mushfiqur Rahim and Liton Das to take them to safer shores and boy, did they deliver! Das reached his maiden ton in Tests and Rahim has complimented him well, as he is on 82 as well. This duo has raised a 204-run stand and would be looking to swell Bangladesh's score up to a big, big number on Day 2.

What a day this has been for Bangladesh! They will be mighty pleased with the effort shown by Das and Rahim as after starting off poorly, these two have steered the Bangla ship to a great position on Day 1 of this Test. Not the best day for the visitors, but the game is still in their grasp and they will need to fight back quickly on Day 2.

As we head back, some Pakistani players congratulate Liton Das. Great spirit of cricket on display by the visitors. STUMPS ON DAY 1!

Liton Das gets to his maiden Test century and the crowd are going bonkers. He raises his bat pointing towards the sky. This has been a knock of the highest quality. ...DAY 1, SESSION 3...

Pakistan's bowlers did nothing wrong, to be honest. There were freebies offered on a couple of occasions but other than that, they did pretty much alright. The pitch is getting easier to bat on and the bowlers are not getting anything out of the pitch. The spinners did get some turn but to no success. They will now look to break this partnership to get back the momentum. Will they be able to do so? Do join us at 3 pm local (9 am GMT) for the final session to find out.

What a session for Bangladesh! Great resilience showed by Mushfiqur Rahim and Liton Das! After being reduced to 49/4, it was up to these two batters to rebuild the innings and they managed to do that successfully. They fought hard and kept going along. Liton Das showed intent and played a couple of aggressive shots while Mushfiqur Rahim tried to keep the scoreboard ticking. Eventually, both the batters got to their respective half centuries and will look to continue to bat throughout the final session.

A torrid start for Bangladesh in this session and to this Test as they have lost 4 wickets in no time. Their openers looked hasty and nervous right at the start and they did not last for long out there. It looked like Najmul Hossain Shanto and Mominul Haque would steady things but from a position of 47/2, they slipped to 49/4 and lost these both too. Pakistan were smelling blood and could have had another one but the duo of Mushfiqur Rahim and Liton Das ensured that they made it to Lunch unscathed after that poor start. They have only raised 20 in their stand so far but have shown great resistance and would be looking to continue the same. Will they be able to do so? Or will Pakistan build on this session's work? Join us at 12.40 pm local (6.40 am GMT) for the second session of the day.

Pakistan's session, by and large! Had someone told them that they would snare 4 wickets by Lunch on Day 1, then they would have taken it with both hands. Their pacers and spinners, both, have bowled with authority and have troubled the Bangla batters throughout the first session. With the exception of Nauman Ali, all of their bowlers got a wicket to their name and it shows how all of them have combined to inflict damage on the hosts. But, special mention has to be given to Shaheen Afridi, who has been on fire right from the first ball of the Test, and even though he has only one wicket to his name, his impact has been top-notch. Hasan Ali has been slightly expensive in his quota of 5 overs, whereas, the other bowlers have been economical.

On the pads, nudged to square leg for a single.
Loopy ball, on off. Das presses forward and defends it solidly off the front foot.
Outside off, turning away. Das lets this one go. Sharp turn on that occasion.
Outside off, Rahim prods and defends it towards point. A maiden!
Length ball, on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Short ball this time from Hasan Ali, on off. Rahim ducks underneath easily.
Good-length ball, on off. Rahim defends it back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, on off. Rahim works it towards covers.
Length ball, on middle. Rahim drops this one on the leg side.
Full and outside off, turning away. Das lets it be.
Loopy ball, outside off. Das leaves it alone.
Loopy ball, on middle. Das stays on the back foot and defends it watchfully.
Full and on middle, blocked out.
On off, pushed to covers.
Short and outside off, Das camps back and cuts it through cover-point. The fielder gives it a chase and keeps it down to a couple.

Short of a length, on off. Rahim ducks too early on that occasion and Shaheen Afridi has a wry smile about this. He is continuing with his back-of-a-length delivery which indicates he wants another wicket here.
Full and outside off, Rahim shoulders arms to that.
Short of a length, on middle. Rahim defends it down onto the pitch.
Short ball, on middle. Rahim ducks under it.
Back of a length, on off. Das hops and taps it to point for a quick single.
On a length, on middle. Das covers the line and presses this to mid off.
Flatter ball, on middle. Rahim stays back and defends it out. Another maiden for Nauman Ali!
Floats it up, on off. Rahim defends it watchfully.
On middle, kept out.
Just short! Loopy ball, on off. Rahim looks to defend but the ball takes off the outside edge. Played it with soft hands and thus, the ball does not carry to the first slip fielder.
Loopy ball, on off. Rahim presses forward and blocks.
Tosses it up, outside off. An easy leave for Rahim.
Good-length ball, on off. Das taps it towards covers.
Short of a length, angling away, on off. Das sways away from the line and leaves it alone.
Short again, on middle. Das sits under it and evades it comfortably.
Short ball, on middle. Das ducks under it.
Back of a length, around off, nipping away. Liton Das looks to defend but misses. The ball whizzes past the outside edge.
Short of a length on leg, Rahim looks to tuck it away but misses. The ball goes off his thigh pad to short fine leg. The batters take a leg bye.
Full and on middle, driven towards covers. A maiden!
Angling in on leg, Das defends it out.
Full and on middle, Das presses forward and blocks it out.
Outside off, dabbed to point.
Loopy ball, on middle. Das pushes it on the off side off the back foot.
Floats it up, on middle. Das stays solid in his defence.
Short of a length, on middle. Rahim defends it on the off side.
On off, Rahim knocks it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, on off. Rahim defends this down to the pitch.
Back of a length again, on off. Rahim drops this down with soft hands.
Back of a length, on off. Rahim stays on the back foot and defends.
Shaheen Afridi (5-1-15-1) is back into the attack.
FOUR! Poor line from Shaheen Afridi! Bowls it down the leg side, Mushfiqur Rahim looks to tuck but misses. The ball brushes off his thigh pad and races away to the fine leg fence.
Slower through the air, outside off. Rahim drives it to deep point for a single.
Sliding in on middle and leg. Rahim rocks back and plays this to mid-wicket.
On middle, Rahim nudges it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, no turn at all. Rahim leaves it untouched.
Tosses it up, on middle. Rahim watchfully blocks it out.
Loopy ball, on off. Rahim presses forward and defends it to the off side.
Change. Nauman Ali will have a go now!
On middle, worked behind square on the leg side for a single to end the over.
Good-length around off, Rahim defends.
On a length outside off, Rahim has no interest in playing at this.
Around off, pushed to covers.
On a length on middle, worked off the pads through mid-wicket. Two taken before the fielder can cut it off.
Outside off, an easy leave for Rahim.
FOUR! The timing on this shot was sublime. Very full this time, around off, Liton Das gets underneath this and thumps this one through covers for a boundary.
On middle, the ball spins in, Das moves inside the line and Mohammad Rizwan dives to his left and stops the ball.
Now, Liton Das goes on the back foot and smothers the ball out on the deck.
Flatter this time, outside off and spins in slightly, kept out by Liton.
Slightly shorter and outside off, dabbed towards point by Das.
Floated, around off, kept out.
Das gets off the mark! On middle and leg, clipped behind square leg for three runs.
Bowled in the area of uncertainty and Das has no issues in leaving this alone.
Angled into the off and middle pole, knocked to the leg side.
Fuller outside off, left alone.
The new batter in is Liton Das.

OUT! CAUGHT! Seems like 14 is the cursed number for the Bangladeshi batters as this is the third batter who loses his wicket on the score of 14. Pakistan are well on top in this session and they have already snared 4 wickets so far. Faheem Ashraf hurls across a slightly shortish delivery, outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto stands tall and slaps this one towards the point fielder. Sajid Khan dives ahead and takes this one. The Pakistanis are celebrating but the umpires converge and just want to ensure that this catch is a clean one and so, they ask the TV umpire for guidance, with their soft signal being out. Replays suggest that Khan's fingers were underneath the ball when he took the catch and hence, out is the decision.
Commentary.Howout: c Sajid Khan b Faheem Ashraf

Commentary.Commentary: The umpires want to check if the catch is being taken cleanly. The soft signal is OUT. The third umpire checks for the No Ball first but no issues there. Replay shows that Sajid Khan has his fingers underneath and he is happy enough to show out on the big screen.
On middle, NHS keeps it out.
Flatter around off, Rahim blocks it out. A great over by Sajid!
Strayed on the pads now, easily clipped through square leg for one.
Floated on off, defended out.
Around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up, on middle, gently eased to the right of mid on for a quick single.
Mushfiqur Rahim is the new batsman in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! The review works out for Pakistan and the third one falls down for the hosts. Also the big wicket of the skipper, Mominul Haque. Khan floats this one up, lands it fuller around off, Haque presses forward and looks to defend but the ball spins away very nicely and whistles past the outside edge of Haque to Rizwan, who collects this, and the Pakistan contingent are up in celebration. Wait a minute, the umpire is unmoved right now. He does not think there was any bat on this. Babar Azam goes for the review straightaway and as soon as you see the replays, you know why they were so confident. A clear spike on UltraEdge and the on-field decision has been overturned.
Commentary.Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Sajid Khan

Commentary.Commentary: Pakistan have taken a review for caught behind. They seem very confident about this and already started celebrating. UltraEdge shows there is a spike as the ball passes the bat. The on-field decision will be reversed.
Najmul Hossain Shanto pushes this length delivery to the cover region.
Back of a length, around off, kept out nicely by Shanto.
Good-length delivery, on off, defended out well.
Fuller, slightly outside off, Shanto gets his front foot ahead and leaves it.
Around off, pushed to the leg side.
FOUR! Super shot. On a fuller length, just around the off pole, Najmul Hossain Shanto presents the full face of the blade and creams this through mid off for a boundary.
A maiden for Sajid Khan! Slider which skids on, Haque brings out his bat in time and blocks this one out.
Flatter ball, angling in middle and leg. Haque gets a good stride forward and defends it out.
Flatter and fuller, on off. Haque presses forward and blocks.

Drinks! This is just the start that Pakistan would have been looking for as they have snared 2 wickets and are looking good to take some more. For Bangladesh, Najmul Hossain Shanto and Mominul Haque would be looking to ride the storm until the Lunch break.
Tosses it up, outside off. Haque defends it on the off side.
Slower and angling in, Haque defends it with soft hands.
Loopy ball, outside off, some extra bounce there. Mominul Haque looks to cut but gets beaten on the outside edge.

Nice shot! Fuller and straighter, on middle. Mominul Haque covers the line, presents the full face of the bat, and drives it past the bowler. Shaheen Afridi gives it a chase and parries it back to the other fielder. Three runs taken.
Short of a length, outside off, angling away, Mominul Haque leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Short ball from Ashraf this time, on middle. Mominul Haque ducks and evades it with ease.
Length ball, outside off. Haque lets it be.
On a length, around off. Haque leaves it alone.
Full and outside off, Haque shoulders arms to that one.
Full and on leg, Shanto defends it on the leg side.
Floats it up, on middle. Haque clips it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Loopy ball, on middle. Haque blocks it out.
Short and outside off, Mominul Haque rocks back and cuts it through covers for a couple of runs.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.

NOT OUT! Tosses it up nicely, on middle and leg. Mominul Haque presses forward and looks to defend but misses. He gets hit on the pads. Sajid Khan pleads the umpire for lbw but he is not interested. Pakistan and Co. discuss and they opt for a review at the last second. UltraEdge says that there is no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows wickets missing as the ball was going down the leg side. Pakistan lose their review.
A very late call for a review by Babar Azam to check this LBW appeal. No bat on this suggests UltraEdge. Wickets missing shows Ball Tracker and Pakistan lose a review.
Change from both ends, then. Time for some spin as Sajid Khan will roll his arm!
A maiden to begin with for Faheem Ashraf! Good-length ball, on off. Shanto prods and blocks it towards covers.
Full again, outside off. Shanto leaves it alone.
Fuller in length, on off. Shanto pushes it to short extra cover.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.

JAFFA! What a beautiful delivery! Good-length ball, nipping away from the left-hander, on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto gets all squared up as he tries to defend. The ball zips past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper.
Length ball, on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto drives it but finds the extra cover fielder.

Fuller in length, on middle and leg, nipping back in. Najmul Hossain Shanto flicks it towards deep mid-wicket. A fielder gives it a chase and manages to save the boundary as he pushes the ball back in right in time. Three runs taken.
Change in bowling. Faheem Ashraf is introduced into the attack!
On a length, outside off. Shanto pushes it towards short extra cover.
On off, Shanto blocks it out.
On a length, on off. Shanto gets behind the line of the ball and knocks it back to the bowler.
Full and on middle and leg, Shanto defends it on the leg side.
Length ball, outside off. Shanto lets it sail through.
Fuller, on off. Haque pushes it to mid on.
A touch fuller, on leg. Shanto works it to fine leg and gets to the other end.
Short ball from Shaheen Afridi this time, on middle. Najmul Hossain Shanto ducks underneath.
Fuller in length, on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto drives it back to the bowler who stops the ball on his followthrough.
On a length around off. Najmul Hossain Shanto pushes it towards covers.
On a length, going down the leg side. Najmul Hossain Shanto misses his flick.
The captain, Mominul Haque walks out now.

OUT! LBW! Good-length ball, around off and middle, coming back in sharply. Shadman Islam looks to work it on the leg side but misses. He gets rapped on the pads. Hasan Ali appeals for LBW and the umpire straightaway raises his dreaded finger. Shadman Islam consults his partner and ultimately takes the review. UltraEdge shows that there was no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows all three reds and Shadman Islam has to walk back to the pavilion and the hosts lose a review too. Both the openers are back in the hut and Pakistan have started well, getting two wickets early.

Review time! Shadman Islam has been given out for LBW and he takes the review. UltraEdge shows that there was no bat on this. Ball Tracker shows three reds and Islam has to take the long way back to the shed.
Around off, Shadman Islam defends this one without any trouble.
On a length, on leg. Najmul Hossain Shanto works it to square leg for a single.
Good-length ball, on off, nipping back in at 133.5 kph. Najmul Hossain Shanto blocks this one to the off side.
Length ball, around off, coming back in. Najmul Hossain Shanto watches the ball closely and makes a leave.
Good inward movement, on off. Shanto presses forward and defends.
Outside off, Islam raises his blade and lets the cherry pass.
Short of a length, on off, SI keeps it out.
Down the leg side, the flick is missed.
Shadman Islam has just blocked that from his crease.

EDGY FOUR! Bangladesh just keep scoring the boundaries here. Outside off, on a good length, Shadman Islam wants to defend but gets squared up. The outside edge is induced and the ball sneaks through between gully and the slip cordon to the ropes.

Short of a length, on the fifth stump channel, Shadman Islam defends inside the line and misses. An appeal from the slip cordon. Don't really know for what, since there was a big, big gap between bat and ball.
On the off pole, on a length, Shanto looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto his pad.
On middle, flicked to fine leg for one.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Around off, defended out solidly.
FOUR! The boundaries are coming by nicely for the hosts. A touch shorter this time, around off, Shadman Islam stands tall and powers this one through mid-wicket. Boundary.
Around off, kept out by Islam.
Way outside off, slightly shorter, left alone.
FOUR! That is quite a way to open your account. Shaheen Afridi errs this time and bowls it on the pads, Najmul Hossain Shanto whips this one wonderfully through square leg and fetches a boundary.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Najmul Hossain Shanto walks out to bat at No.3.

OUT! CAUGHT! That was a snorter of the delivery and Pakistan get their first wicket early on. Shaheen Afridi has been troubling the openers so far and his hard work has paid off. He sticks with the back-of-a-length delivery again, it is bowled around off and the ball shoots up after hitting the deck. Saif Hassan gets his blade high up, looking to defend it, but the ball catches the shoulder of the bat and loops up near short leg. Abid Ali has the easiest of takes and Pakistan send back one of Bangladesh's openers.
Commentary.Howout: c Abid Ali b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! Confident stroke from Hassan. This is pitched up by Afridi, around off, Saif Hassan plays this gently through covers and bags a boundary.
Good delivery again from Shaheen. Short of a length, around off, the ball lands and jags away and bounces a tad more too. Misses the outside edge of Hassan.
Bowled in the fourth stump line, an easy leave for Islam.

Loud shot for LBW but turned down! Around off and middle, on a length, the ball jags back in this time, Islam misses his flick and is pinged on the pad. An appeal but the umpire says no. A discussion between Hasan Ali, Mohammad Rizwan, and Babar Azam but they do not take the review.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! That looked so good. Islam's confidence will be given a boost due to this. Outside off, on a length, Shadman Islam presses forward and eases this through mid off. A player gives it chase but the ball wins the race.
Good-length ball, on off, played towards covers.
On off, Hassan plays this through point for one.
Around off, on a length, pushed through mid off for one.
Fuller, outside off, Hassan makes a leave.
Shadman Islam gets underway. Outside off, steered through point for a single.
Back of a length, on the fourth stump line, the ball lands and jags away slightly. Again, Shadman Islam misses his poke and the ball steams past his outside edge to the keeper.
Short of a length, around off, tapped to point.
Way outside off, an easy leave for Islam.
On middle, pushed away to the leg side. 8 off Ali's first over!
FOUR! Another boundary. Saif Hassan has begun well here with two boundaries. Too straight this time, on middle and leg, gently nudged to the fine leg fence.
On a length, on middle, Hassan looks to tuck but gets a leading edge to the off side.
FOUR! Bangladesh and Saif Hassan start with a boundary. Hasan Ali serves this on the pad, on a length, Saif Hassan just has to clip this gently and the ball speeds away to the fine leg boundary.
Again, on a length and outside off, Saif does not want to fiddle with this and makes a leave.
Good-length delivery, outside off, easily left alone by Saif.
Hasan Ali to bowl from the other end.
Maiden for Afridi! Fuller, but way outside off, moves away as Islam leaves it alone.

Play and a miss! The fourth stump line is working out for Afridi. It is bowled on a length and it straightens off the seam, Islam looks to have a poke but misses. A smile on Shaheen's face. He is already smelling blood.
A bumper this time, on middle and leg, Islam ducks down and lets it be.
Outside off, on a length, some away movement again and Islam misses his defensive push away.
Better from Islam. This is bowled slightly straighter and Islam defends it out.

JAFFA FIRST UP! Woahhhhh! What a delivery to begin from Shaheen Afridi. Cracker. Afridi serves a back-of-a-length delivery, around off, it lands and nips away beautifully. Shadman Islam looks to defend but gets squared up as the ball whistles past the outside edge to the keeper.

We are set to begin! The umpires make their way to the middle. The Pakistani players stride out to the middle. Shadman Islam and Saif Hassan are the openers for Bangladesh. Shaheen Afridi will open the attack with the ball. Here we go...

Babar Azam, the Pakistan skipper, says that they would have batted first too but says that the toss is not in their hands. Adds that there is a good covering of grass on the deck and they will look to take quick wickets. Feels that consistency matters and they are looking to continue their good work. Informs that Imam-ul-Haq misses out and Abdullah Shafique will be making his debut.

Mominul Haque, the skipper of Bangladesh says that they will bat first. Mentions that Chattogram is always good for batting and that's why they want to bat first. Tells that they will miss Tamim, Shakib and Taskin but it is a great opportunity for other players to step up and informs that Yasir Ali will make his debut.

Pitch Report - Ed Rainsford says that the outfield is looking wonderful. Mentions that the groundstaff have done a phenomenal job and there is a lot of covering of grass. Tells that it is an excellent batting track and the surface holds together pretty well. Reckons that the captain winning the toss should bat first.

Bangladesh (Playing XI) - Shadman Islam, Najmul Hossain Shanto, Mominul Haque (C), Mushfiqur Rahim, Liton Das (WK), Yasir Ali (Debut), Mehidy Hasan, Taijul Islam, Abu Jayed, Ebadot Hossain, Saif Hassan.
Pakistan (Playing XI) - Abdullah Shafique (Debut), Abid Ali, Azhar Ali, Babar Azam (C), Fawad Alam, Mohammad Rizwan (WK), Faheem Ashraf, Nauman Ali, Hasan Ali, Shaheen Afridi, Sajid Khan.
TOSS - It's time for the all-important coin toss now. Up goes the coin and lands in the favor of Bangladesh. They have elected to BAT first.
Update - Some news coming in from Bangladesh. There was an earthquake at Chattogram earlier this morning but fortunately players from both teams are reported to be safe.

Pakistan have been nothing less than a phenomenal side in the recent years. They didn't put a foot wrong in the T20 World Cup until they run into the eventual champions Australia, who pushed them out of the semi final. Then they whitewashed Bangladesh 3-0 in the T20Is and would be now eager to don the white jersey. They have a plenty of reliable options in Fawad Alam, Azhar Ali and Mohammad Rizwan alongside Babar Azam. They also have Shaheen Afridi who can make the ball talk in any conditions alongwith Hasan Ali. Pakistan already have 12 points in their account as they won a Test earlier this year against West Indies. After the T20Is, the side would be eyeing another clean sweep now. Will they be able to do that? We will find out. Stay tuned for further updates.

Bangladesh are not being able to emulate performances even half as impressive as they did against Australia and New Zealand earlier this year. First, they lost all their matches in the Super 12 and then lost 0-3 to Pakistan in the T20Is. They would now hope for a change of fortunes with the format change. Although, it won't get any easier for them as Mahmudullah called retirement while Tamim Iqbal and Shakib Al Hasan are out with injury. As if that is not a sufficient dent, Taskin Ahmed and Shoriful Islam will sit out too. It is going to be nothing but a tough task for the Bangla Tigers but they would be keen to kick start their World Test Championship cycle with a win and get some points.

Hello and a warm welcome to Day 1 of the first Test between Bangladesh and Pakistan. The first Test is set to be played at Chattogram. After a 3-0 clean sweep in the shortest format, Pakistan would want to stamp their authority while Bangladesh would want to kick start their World Test Championship cycle with a win though they have got a lot on their plate as they have a plethora of big names missing from the squad due to various reasons. Can Bangladesh spring a surprise? Or will Pakistan set the record straight in red ball cricket as well? All the questions will get answered over the course of the next five days.
...Day 1, Session 1...

We are back for the final session of Day 3!  The Pakistan players make their way out to the middlle. Bangladesh opening batters Shadman Islam and Saif Hassan are there in the middle too. Shaheen Afridi to start for Pakistan.
...DAY 3, SESSION 3...

Bangladesh had a tiring Day 2 but they got wickets in heap in the morning session. Taijul Islam wasted no time and quickly removed Abdullah Shafique and Azhar Ali off consecutive balls in the first over itself. Mehidy Hasan then joined the party and removed Babar Azam cheaply. Taijul Islam continued to breathe fire as he got the better of Fawad Alam. The bowlers already got 4 wickets in the first session and post Lunch, the bowlers continued their good work as Ebadot Hossain quickly removed Mohammad Rizwan while Taijul Islam continued his fine form getting two more wickets. He ended with seven wickets to his name and was the main guy behind putting Pakistan on the back foot completely. The spinners did the bulk of bowling and reaped rewards but credit goes to Ebadot Hossain as well who kept probing with his tight line and lengths and scalped two wickets as well. The bowlers will be extremely pleased with what they have acheived and now have a lead of 44 runs. Bangladesh bowlers have done their job and it is upto their batters now to come out to bat with positive intent and extend the lead as much as they can. What does the final session have in store for us? Do join us back at 3.20 local (9.20am GMT) to find out.

Pakistan will be disappointed given the start they had. From 145-0, they slipped to 182-4. Abdullah Shafique and Azhar Ali both departed in the first over itself of the morning session. After that, Babar Azam and Fawad Alam too couldn't fight for long and made their way back to the hut. Abid Ali continued on his merry way from one end while Mohammad Rizwan batted out till Lunch despite a few nervy moments. Post Lunch, Rizwan made his way back to the pavilion soon. Abid Ali was dropped on 133 at short leg but got out in the same over. After that, Faheem Ashraf milked some runs along with the lower order but they could not get past the Bangladesh's total and have given them a handy lead of 44 runs.
That was the last over of the extend session and Taijul Islam has got a wicket. Pakistan have been bundled out for 286 and Taijul Islam ends with a seven-fer to his name. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 3!

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! It's all over! Taijul Islam bags his seventh wicket and is delighted and so are the other Bangladesh  players. Tossed up delivery around leg. Faheem Ashraf looks to sweep but gets a faint edge and Liton Das behind the stumps moves across quickly. He somehow manages to pouch the ball between his legs. A good innings by Faheem Ashraf comes to an end and Bangladesh after the first innings are leading by 44 runs.
Commentary.Howout: c Liton Das b Taijul Islam

Around off, blocked out.
Full and outside off. Shaheen Afridi pushes it towards covers.
Flighted, just outside off. Faheem Ashraf defends it back to the bowler.

On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, on middle. Faheem Ashraf defends it on the leg side.

On the pads, tucked to short fine leg.
Full again, on off. Shaheen Afridi presses forward and blocks it out.

Pakistan had the worst possible start as the debutant Abdullah Shafique and Azhar Ali departed in the very first over. Babar Azam along with Abid Ali stayed at the crease for some time but the former departed soon as Pakistan were reduced to 169-3 from 146-0. In the meanwhile, Abid Ali brought his fourth century at the other end and continued to hold one end up. But Fawad Alam who has been in superb form since his comeback in the international cricket also followed his captain back to the hut soon. Since then, Mohammad Rizwan has joined Abid Ali and the duo has survived few nervy moments and assured that Pakistan did not lose any further wickets. Day 3 of this Test match has followed the same pattern of the first two days of batting side losing wickets in heap in the first session. Will the second session be dominated by the batters? Or will Bangladesh spinners continue their march? Do join us at 12.40 local time (6.40 am GMT) to find out.

A very fruitful session for Bangladesh as they have managed to pick four wickets in the morning session. Taijul Islam started on the perfect note as he trapped both Abdullah Shafique and Azhar Ali in the very first over of the day. Ebadot Hossain bowling from the other end also kept the pressure on. Mehidy Hasan then joined his spin partner and got the big fish, Babar Azam straightaway. The spin duo continued to wreak havoc as Taijul Islam then got the wicket of Fawad Alam. He bowled throughout the session from one end and with the pitch helping spinners, expect the spin twins to bowl the bulk of the overs in the next session too. Pakistan still trail by 127 runs and Bangladesh will be looking to put more pressure on them in post-lunch session.

Khaled Mahmud Sujan, the manager of Bangladesh cricket team is up for a chat. He says that Test match is all about getting a breakthrough. Mentions that there might be moisture in the morning session so the bowlers will look to exploit the conditions and break the partnership. Tells that if they stick to the plans, they might get the wicket and put pressure back on Pakistan. Adds that from 49-4, Mushfiqur Rahim and Liton Das batted brilliantly and put them in a good position. Says that they were looking for a score around 400 but are happy with what they have put.

The overnight batters for Pakistan will look to continue on their merry way and their first task will be to bring down the deficit as they still trail by 185 runs and then they would look to stock up as many runs as possible. Abid Ali is inching closer to his century whereas the debutant is playing a good knock from the other end and would also be keen to get to the three digit figure. Given the batting that is still to come for Pakistan, they are in a commendable position and if Bangladesh soon cannot find a way to scalp a few wickets, they would be put under more pressure. The pitch is only getting better and better to bat but there is some purchase for the spinners and they will look to take the advantage and break the opening stand. An exciting day of cricket awaits us. Stay tuned as we bring you more updates.

Hello and a warm welcome to the coverage of Day 3 of the first Test between Bangladesh and Pakistan. Day 2 proved to be a fruitful one for the visitors as first they quickly scalped 6 wickets in the morning session and bundled Bangladesh out for 330 with Hasan Ali being star with the ball having a five-fer to his name. After that, Abid Ali and Abdullah Shafique batted whole two sessions and are unbeaten with a 145-run stand. Let's see what's in store for us today…
...DAY 3, SESSION 1…

Right then! Pakistan are in the driver's seat and they will look to cross the trail and then extend the lead. For Bangladesh, breaking this partnership followed by a couple of key wickets remains the goal. Day 3, also known as the moving day will start at 10 am local (4 am GMT). But the build-up will begin much earlier. Do join us for that. Cheers!

A pretty tiring day for the hosts! Bangladesh batters would have hoped for their overnight batters to continue for long but that wasn't to be as Liton Das departed early. Wickets started to tumble and Rahim also couldn't march along and missed out on a century falling short by 9 runs. Mehidy Hasan tried to rebuild the innings and ensured Bangladesh breach the 300-run mark but ran out of partners and they folded for 330. Coming out to bowl, they found no success. Their bowlers started well but didn't get enough from the pitch to trouble the Pakistani opening pair. The spinners did get some aid from the pitch as the ball started to misbehave but the Pakistani batters were too good to play it out. Bangladesh will have to access their plans coming onto Day 3 as there's still plenty of batting left in Pakistan's tank and if they do not get wickets quickly, it would only further sink their ship.

Pakistan pocket another session! By far, it has been their day! First, they started the morning session with a bang as their pacers got the remaining six wickets and Hasan Ali was particularly exceptional with the ball as he ended the innings with a five-fer to his name. The visitors then had the perfect middle session as Abdullah Shafique and Abid Ali batted till Tea without any trouble though the former, on 9, got a reprieve as Bangladesh didn't challenge an lbw call which could have been overturned. Post that, there were hardly any chances created and Abid Ali notched up his fifty and the debutant looked unflustered at the crease. The openers continued to milk runs with ease and later Abdullah Shafique also got to his half-century on debut. The duo remained unscathed for the entire day. Bad lights meant that Abid Ali will have to wait until tomorrow to get his ton. Pakistan will look to continue to pile runs as they still trail by 185 runs.

Bangladesh have toiled hard in this session but without any success. A wicket or two would have reassured them slightly but without a single wicket to their name, this session belongs to the visitors. The pacers started well but did not trouble the Pakistani opening pair too much. The spinners have not really made the ball turn a lot, though they have bowled decently. They had a chance to grab a wicket but they opted against taking the review for their LBW shout, which replays indicated would have been out. Will the duo for Pakistan continue their good work and cut down the deficit? Or will the Bangla Tigers have some tea and come out invigorated and snare a couple of quick wickets? Join us for the third session at 3 pm local (9 am GMT) to find out.

We are back! Bangladesh players form a huddle and stride out to the middle to take their respective positions. Abdullah Shafique and Abid Ali are the openers for Pakistan. Taijul Islam will start the proceedings.

Hasan Ali started the morning session on a bright note scalping the wicket of Mushfiqur Rahim. Post Lunch, Liton Das and Nurul Hasan scored runs at brisk rate but Pakistan bowlers did not take much time wrapping things up. Sajid Khan scalped the wicket of the substitute, Nurul Hasan and then Shaheen Afridi scalped two wickets in an over to get to his five-fer. The bowlers have done their job and Pakistan are in the driver's seat now. They have ample of time to chase down 202. This Test match has been full of twists and turns. Do we have another twist and can Bangladesh defend this down? We will find out. Do join us shortly.

Just like Bangladesh's first innings, they were put under pressure in the second innings as they were reeling at 23-4. Mushfiqur Rahim tried to repair the innings but failed to do so as he got out in the first over of the morning session. After that, Yasir Ali did well to score some runs but got hit on the helmet and had to be taken off the field. Post Lunch, Liton Das and Nurul Hasan started to play aggressively and made their intentions very clear. The former also brought up his half century in the process. Nurul Hasan tried to go big but departed later. After that, Das and Taijul Islam continued to motor along and got the lead to go past 200 but then they lost wickets in cluster and were bundled out for 157.

Bangladesh started the second session with a flurry of boundaries but bowlers of Pakistan quickly wrapped things up. They will be very pelased with the efforts and now have almost four and a half sessions to chase the target of 202 which Bangladesh have set. Shaheen Afridi leads his side off the field and raises the ball as he ended with a five-fer.

The ball goes behind the stumps and Mohammad Rizwan whips the bails off as Taijul Islam is out of his crease by some margin. Third wicket for Sajid Khan and Bangladesh have been bundled out for 157 here. Pakistan need 202 to win this Test match!
Commentary.Howout: st Mohammad Rizwan b Sajid Khan

Pakistan are just one wicket away now from bundling out Bangladesh. Shaheen Afridi is the man again for Pakistan who delivers under the pressure.

...DAY 4, SESSION 2…

Mushfiqur Rahim started the day with a boundary but departed soon after, off the third ball of the day. Liton Das joined Yasir Ali and both started scoring runs at a brisk rate and took Bangladesh lead past 100. But just when debutant Yasir Ali was looking good, he got hit on his helmet off the bowling of Shaheen Afridi and had to walk off the field. Mehidy Hasan joined Liton Das and both had a good brief partnership but Mehidy lost his wicket just at the stroke of the lunch. Overall a decent session for Bangladesh as they have taken their lead to 159 runs and will be looking to pile on more runs in the next session. It has been a riveting session of Test cricket and do join us at 12.40 pm local (6.40 am GMT) for the post-lunch session.

Pakistan made the perfect start to the session as Hasan Ali took the wicket of Mushfiqur Rahim in the very first over. But apart from Shaheen Afridi, other bowlers failed to put enough pressure on Bangladesh batters as the runs started flowing. The bowlers were inconsistent with their line and lengths and spinners especially failed to trouble Bangladesh batters. Shaheen Afridi bowled some good short stuff and hit Yasir Ali on his helmet and had to walk off the field. Mehidy Hasan walked in and the partnership started building again but Sajid Khan just minutes before the lunch break got an important wicket of Mehidy Hasan. They have taken two wickets in this session and will be looking to finish off the Bangladesh innings as early as possible in the post-lunch session as anything more than 200 to chase can get tricky on this pitch.

Russell Domingo is down for the chat. He says that there is a still long way to go. He adds that it is 50-50 at the moment but they are still positive. He says that bowlers were fantastic yesterday and for today runs are important. He adds that 150 runs more will be important and the first hour will be crucial.

Shaheen Afridi is up for a chat. He says that he and Hasan Ali try to pitch in the good areas. Mentions that the wicket is really good for batting and is very slow so that try to bowl on good lengths. Tells that with the new ball, there is always a chance for swing so he tries to bowl with pace. Adds that he enjoys each and every format of the game. Says that Bangladesh have a good spin unit and they try to play the game and enjoy cricket.

With the match hanging in balance, the first session today holds the key. If Bangladesh batters can play out the first session without much damage they can put Pakistan under real pressure after that. The pitch has assistance for both seamers and spinners and it will become harder and harder to bat as the day progresses. From Pakistan point of view, they would like to finish the Bangladesh innings as early as possible as chasing anything over 200 in this pitch on the last day can get very tricky. The key wicket here is Mushfiqur Rahim and if Pakistan get him out early here, then the road ahead can get easy for them. A very interesting day of Test cricket awaits us as the match can go either way and Day 4 might well be the deciding day of this Test match. Stay tuned for more updates.

Hello and a warm welcome to the coverage of Day 4 of the first Test between Bangladesh and Pakistan. Day 3 turned out to be a moving day of this Test as Bangladesh bundled out Pakistan for 286 taking 10 wickets in just two sessions. The star of the show was Taijul Islam as he bagged seven wickets to dismantle Pakistan hopes of taking a lead in this Test match. Abid Ali scored his fourth century but at the end of the second session, it was Bangladesh who finished with a lead of 44 runs. In the post-tea session, it was time for Pakistan bowlers to rule the show and they did that in style as they picked four wickets and gave away just 39 runs. The match is hanging right in the balance as Bangladesh lead by 83 runs with 6 wickets in hand. Which team will inch ahead at the end of Day 4? We shall find out soon.

Right then! That's the coverage from this day! Pakistan pacers have done well but they need to make sure that they don't let a partnership grow now like the first innings as it might take the game away from them. Bangladeshi batters will look to pile as many runs as possible from here on and extend their lead. Day 4 will begin at 10 am local (4 am GMT). But the build-up will begin much in advance. Do join us for that. Cheers!

Earlier in the day, Taijul Islam  was the star of the day for Bangladesh as he bagged a seven-wicket haul and kept Pakistan batters on the back foot throughout the day. For Pakistan, it was Abid Ali  who got to his fourth century as wickets kept falling at the other end. There was some resistance shown by Faheem Ashraf at the end of their innings but eventually, Bangladesh bowlers managed to take 44 runs lead for their team at the end of the first innings. The game is evenly matched as 150 odd runs more by Bangladesh from here will make things quite interesting tomorrow. Remember, Pakistan will be batting last on this pitch and there will be enough turn for Bangladesh bowlers to make a match out of it.

Bangladesh top order have completely outdone the hard work their bowlers did earlier in the day. The top order failed to cope up with quality pace bowling by Pakistan bowlers and departed without troubling the scorers just like the first innings. Mushfiqur Rahim has again been the rock for Bangladesh, showing good technique and temperament while other batters failed to match him. Yasir Ali joined him and the duo managed to get Bangladesh to stumps without further damage. They have a lead of 83 runs and will like to build from here to give their bowlers a decent score to bowl at.

A good bowling display by Pakistan in this final session. Their bowlers were right on the money from the start and both Shaheen Afridi and Hasan Ali troubled Bangladesh top order with their swing and pace. Shaheen Afridi especially was lethal and combined his swing and seam with fearsome short bowling. He got three top wickets while Hasan Ali got the crucial wicket of Bangladesh captain, Mominul Haque. Nauman Ali and Faheem Ashraf  kept the pressure on after that but Bangladesh managed to survive without further damage.

Babar Azam, the skipper of Pakistan, says that he is very happy with the show of his team. Adds that Shaheen Afridi and Hasan Ali had a brilliant game. Says that they would look to improve on bowling consistently when the opposition batters get a partnership going. Praises Abdullah Shafique for the way he built his innings and played on his debut. Also praises Abid Ali for the way he batted and delivered for his team in both the innings

Abid Ali is the PLAYER OF THE MATCH! He says that 330 runs was the target in the first innings and so they wanted to stay at the wicket and build partnerships. He adds that the domestic performances and experience helped him. He applauds Abdullah Shafique and says he played outstanding cricket and they both were helping each other and he adds that he is happy for him. He says that he is happy to win the match and it would have been great to get a century though.

Mominul Haque, the skipper of Bangladesh, says that they lost the game in the first hour of the first and second innings with the bat. Adds that the pitch remained a good one to bat on throughout and if they had 100 more runs, things could have been different. Says that they need to work on their batting going forward.

Bangladesh started their second innings in the worst possible manner as their top order once again folded but Liton Das was once again responsible for their recovery as he scored a fifty. Shaheen Afridi took a 5-wicket haul for Pakistan to bowl out the hosts for 157. Bangladesh had a pretty big lead of 201 runs and bowling second on this pitch gave them a pretty good chance of defending it against Pakistan but once again, a brilliant opening stand between Abid Ali and Abdullah Shafique gave Bangladesh no chance of defending this total.

Pakistan though started brilliantly with the bat in their first innings. Abid Ali and Abdullah Shafique, with the former scoring a ton, provided them with a brilliant start and they were at 146 for 0 in reply to Bangladesh's 330. But Pakistan had a big collapse of their own as after the openers fell, the middle order folded very early and they were bowled out for 286. Taijul Islam was the wrecker-in-chief as his 7 wickets gave Bangladesh a handy 44-run lead on a pitch that was not very easy to bat on.

Earlier in the game, the bowlers of Pakistan demolished the top order of Bangladesh on Day 1 but the hosts recovered thanks to a brilliant ton by Liton Das and a knock of 91 runs by Mushfiqur Rahim. Had these two senior pros not stepped up, then Bangladesh would have had a low total in the first innings. The star with the ball was Hasan Ali as he took a 5-wicket haul.

Bangladesh, on the other hand, had a very disappointing innings with the ball. They would have wanted to get early wickets to put the middle order of Pakistan under pressure but that did not happen. Mehidy Hasan and Taijul Islam were the only bowlers to take wickets in this innings but it came quite late for them.

What a chase by Pakistan! Chasing more than 200 runs in the last two days was not going to be easy but they have made a mockery of the chase. Abdullah Shafique and Abid Ali were brilliant yet again and their opening stand made sure that they would win this game. Abdullah Shafique missed out on getting a well-deserved ton and so did Abid Ali. But they had done their job and Pakistan won it with ease. What a show by Pakistan in the last innings of the game.

What a game and what a victory for Pakistan! This was a brilliant Test match and both the sides fought hard but in the end, it is Pakistan, who get the win here. A clinical show by them and they have deserved this victory.

Hello and a warm welcome to the coverage of Day 5 of the first Test between Bangladesh and Pakistan. Day 4 turned out to be a decisive day as Pakistan have finally taken the driver’s seat in this Test match after a spirited bowling effort and yet another century stand by their openers. The star of the show with the ball was Shaheen Afridi as he picked his fourth five-wicket haul and bundled out Bangladesh for just 157 to restrict their lead to 201. For Bangladesh, things were looking quite good after the first session but all went downhill after that as the wicket of Nurul Hasan triggered a collapse and they were restricted to much less than what they were looking for. The bowlers barring Taijul Islam failed to create enough chances and by the end of the day, Pakistan needed just 93 runs for the victory. Bangladesh need something special from here on otherwise things can end quite quickly here. Can Bangladesh fight back? We shall find out.

Earlier, in the day, Pakistan bowlers were impressive as they bundled out Bangladesh for 157 runs. Shaheen Afridi was the star with the ball as he took his fourth five-wicket haul and delivered under pressure for Pakistan. Bangladesh, on the other hand, were looking good as Liton Das made a classy fifty under pressure. But once he departed, things finished rather quickly for them. Their bowlers after that have failed to get a breakthrough and things look bleak for them now.

Bangladesh bowlers toiled hard but failed to get a breakthrough. Taijul Islam was again the pick of the bowlers as he created whatever half-chances Bangladesh managed to create. The other spinner Mehidy Hasan failed to match his consistency and that allowed Pakistan batters to get some quick runs. The seamers too were ineffective and leaked runs and that allowed Pakistan batters to score freely without any pressure. It looks difficult for Bangladesh from here on and the match is headed only in one direction unless Bangladesh produce something special from here on.

What a session for Pakistan! Their openers have put them in a driver's seat yet again and this time more decisively. Both of them played some smart cricket combining caution with aggression as they both completed their respective fifties. Abdullah Shafique is only the second player to be involved in a two century partnerships on a debut in a Test match and that shows the impact these two have made on this game. They have 93 more runs to score in this game and Pakistan will be hoping that the openers finish it off as early as possible tomorrow.

Fuller and pushed away to mid on.
Tossed up on off. Abdullah Shafique defends this off the front foot.

Drinks! A good passage of play for Pakistan. Their openers have looked solid and have scored runs at a brisk rate adding to the frustration of the Bangladesh bowlers. Bangladesh spinners are getting enough turn to beat the outside edge of the blade of these batters but have failed to get the breakthrough. Pakistan need 117 runs and have 10 wickets in their tank and a full day left.
Tossed up on middle. Abid Ali presses forward and defends this comfortably.
Full and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
An arm ball, on leg. Abid Ali looks to defend but gets an inside edge to short leg.
Tossed up, outside off. Abid Ali defends it back to the bowler.

In the air, but safe! Loopy ball, on middle. Abdullah Shafique comes down the track and slogs it blindly. The ball goes off the leading edge over covers. The fielder from cover traces back but the ball lands far away from him. A single is taken.

NOT OUT! Taijul Islam bowls a quicker delivery, on leg. Shafique looks to defend but misses. He gets hit on the pads. Taijul Islam pleads the umpire for an lbw but the umpire says no. He is convinced and Mominul Haque opts for a review after discussing it with the bowler. Nothing on UltraEdge. Ball Tracking shows wickets missing and Bangladesh burn their review.

Bangladesh have taken a review for an LBW.  The replay rolls in and UltraEdge shows that there is no bat invloved. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that the ball is missing the stumps. So the decision stays and Bangladesh lose their review.
On the pads this time. Abid Ali defends this to short fine leg.
Flighted delivery on off. Abid Ali defends this back to the bowler.
Fuller and turning into the batter. Abdullah Shafique nudges it behind square on the on side for a single.
Quicker and flatter on middle. Abdullah Shafique blocks it away.
Another shortish length, on off. Pushed to mid off and sets off for a quick single. There is a shy at the bowler's end by the fielder there but misses.
Slightly shorter length. Abid Ali goes deep in his crease and defends it. Low bounce there but Abid does well to block it.
Another tossed up delivery and defended comfortably again off the front foot. Pakistan need 120 runs to win this game now.
Tossed up this time on middle. Defended off the front foot.
On the pads this time and Abdullah Shafique tucks it away to backward square leg.
Shorter length, on off. Punched to deep cover for a single.
FOUR! Tossed up on middle. Abid Ali reaches for it and goes on his knees to slog sweep it towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary. The batters are getting runs quite quickly here
Flatter delivery on off. Turned away to deep square leg for a single.
Change of ends for Taijul Islam.
Tossed up on off. Abid Ali defends this off the front foot.
Shorter length now and Abid Ali goes deep in his crease to punch it towards covers. The batters take two runs as the fielder there cuts it off.
Another loopy delivery around off. Abid Ali defends this towards the off side. Mehidy Hasan runs across and makes sure that no run is taken by the batter.
Tossed up, on off. Abid Ali nicely gets forward and defends it.
Fuller on middle. Abid Ali paddle-sweeps it to long leg for a couple.
Flighted delivery on middle. Abid Ali defends this off the back foot.
Mehidy Hasan (5-1-20-0) is reintroduced into the attack.
Full ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique defends this towards the on side.
FOUR! An even better shot now! Another overpitched delivery on middle and leg. Abdullah Shafique flicks it off his pads wide of mid on for a boundary.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Abdullah Shafique! Half-volley, on leg. Abdullah Shafique just tucks it fine towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Full, on middle and leg. Abdullah Shafique works it to mid-wicket.

Shorter length, outside off. Abdullah Shafique pushes it off the back foot towards covers. Najmul Hossain Shanto there collects the ball and fires in a wide throw at the batter's end and gives away an extra run off an overthrow. Two runs in the end.
On a length, on the pads. Abid Ali works it to square leg and gets a single.
Around leg this time. Abdullah Shafique paddle-sweeps it to fine leg for a couple.
BEATEN! Another flighted delivery on off. Abdullah Shafique presses forward to defend but the ball turns away sharply and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Another loopy delivery around leg. Defended onto the on side.
Nicely tossed up on middle. Defended off the front foot.
Shorter length, on off. Abid Ali pushes it off the back foot towards deep cover for a single.
Tossed up on middle and off. Abid Ali defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
Full ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique drives this off the inside half of his blade to mid on.
Length ball on off and defended off the back foot by Abdullah Shafique.
Back of a length, around off. Abid Ali skips down the track and slaps it to mid on. Mushfiqur Rahim there does well and stops it with a dive. A single taken.
Length ball, on off. Abid Ali solidly defends this off the back foot.
On a length again, on middle and leg. Abid Ali works it to short mid-wicket.
On a length, on off. Abdullah Shafique defends this off the back foot towards the off side and gets a quick single.
Abu Jayed is brought into the attack. He replaces Mehidy Hasan.
Angling in, on middle and leg. Abid Ali defends it watchfully.
Drifting in, on off. Abid Ali blocks it out.
Quicker one, on middle. Abid Ali stays solid in his defence.
An arm ball, on middle and leg. Abid Ali looks to defend off the back foot but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Taijul Islam appeals for an lbw but the umpire is unmoved.
On off, Abid Ali blocks it from the crease.
Loopy ball, full and on off. Abid Ali drives it to mid off.
Tossed up, on off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it with a big stride forward.
On middle, kept out.
FOUR! Pakistan continue to play aggressively! Abdullah Shafique gets to the pitch of the ball by stepping out and smacks it towards wide of long on for a boundary.
Loopy ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Outside off, this time Abid Ali dabs it to third man for three runs. 50 up for Pakistan!
FOUR! Lovely shot! Flighted ball, outside off. Abid Ali leans onto it, opens the face of the bat and creams it through covers for a boundary. He moves into 30's.
Slightly shorter length around off. Pushed to covers for a quick single.
Another quicker delivery around off. Abid Ali gets back to defend it.
Quicker on off. Abid Ali blocks it out.
Beaten! Sharp turn as he bowls this on off, slower in the air. Abid Ali looks to defend it but ball misses the outside edge of his blade.
An arm ball on middle and that kept a little low too. Abid Ali manages to get his bat down in the time.
Nicely tossed up on middle and off. Abid Ali gets forward and defends it towards the off side.
Nicely tosses up, outside off. Abdullah Shafique gets a big stride forward to block.
Flighted ball,outside off. Abid Ali nudges it behind square on the leg side for one.
Tossed up, around off. Abid Ali turns it on the leg side.
Almost carried to mid-wicket! Mehidy Hasan drops it short, on middle. Abid Ali didn't get hold of the pull. Hits high on the bat and the ball bounces just in front of Nurul Hasan at short mid-wicket.
Slower and outside off, Abdullah Shafique pushes it towards covers for one.
Flighted delivery, on middle. Abdullah Shafique tries to play the slog sweep but drags it to mid-wicket as he didn't quite get to the pitch of the ball.
Outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
Taijul Islam is making things happen! This one straightens up after pitching, on off. Abid Ali covers the line and lets it go.

Edged but does not carry! Slower through the air, on off. Abid Ali looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge to the first slip fielder. Played it with soft hands and thus, does not carry.
Flighted delivery, on off. Pushed to mid off.
That turned sharply and some extra bounce as well! Outside off, skids of the pitch and turns away sharply. Abid Ali presses forward and gets beaten on the outside edge.
FOUR! Well-controlled shot! Tossed up ball, on off. Abid Ali gets down on his knee and slog-sweeps it to cow corner for a boundary.
Loopy ball, on middle and leg. Abdullah Shafique defends it off the back foot to short leg. A maiden!
Full and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
On middle, Abdullah Shafique defends it out watchfully.
On the pads, clipped to square leg.
Floated ball, on middle. Tucked to short leg.
Turning in but down the leg side. Easily left alone by Abdullah Shafique.
So spin from both ends. As Mehidy Hasan to bowl from the other end.
Quicker, on middle. Abid Ali reads the length early and fends it on the leg side.
On off, defended out.

Loopy ball, on off. Abid Ali defends it towards covers. He looks for a single but is sent back by Abdullah Shafique. The fielder throws the ball back to the keeper but Abid Ali feels it is on his way and blocks it out with his hands.
Tossed up, on middle, kept out by Abid Ali.
Sliding in, on middle. Abid Ali defends it onto his pads. A mild appeal for an lbw but not given.
Starts with an arm ball, on off. Abid Ali presses forward and blocks it to the off side.

We are back for the final session of the day. The Bangladesh players make their way out to the middle. Pakistan openers Abdullah Shafique and Abid Ali are there in the middle too. Taijul Islam to start for Bangladesh.
...DAY 4, SESSION 3...

Bangladesh started with the star of the first innings, Taijul Islam and the pace of Ebadot Hossain at the other end. Both bowlers bowled well but were unable to get the breakthrough they required. The pitch has enough help to keep them interested and Taijul Islam towards the back end of the session got some balls to turn sharply and they will hope that the next session turns the game their way. Pakistan need another 164 runs and the next session can well turn out to be the deciding session of this Test match. Do join us at 3 pm local (9 am GMT) for the final session of the day.

Excellent session for Pakistan! After wrapping things quite quickly post-lunch, Pakistan openers have done well to negotiate this tough little phase before the Tea. Abid Ali the senior of the two, got some handy boundaries and his debutant partner, Abdullah Shafique once again showed maturity and the skills required at this level. So the first objective to play out this session is cleared now and they will be looking to carry on in the next session as they chase 202 to win the first Test.
Good loopy delivery to end the session but Abdullah Shafique is well forward and defends it right under his eyes. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 4!
Another loopy delivery on off. Abdullah Shafique gets forward and defends comfortably again.
Tossed up on middle. Abdullah Shafique gets forward and defends it.
Quicker on off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it out.
FOUR! Poetry in motion! Tossed up on middle. Abdullah Shafique skips down the track and drives it crisply through covers for a boundary.
Quicker and flatter on off. Abid Ali pushes it off the back foot square on the off side for a single.
Slower in the air, on off. Abdullah Shafique defends this comfortably.
Shorter length around off. Abid Ali just pushes it behind square on the off side and takes a single.
Another loopy delivery on middle. Abid Ali defends this comfortably.
Tossed up on middle and leg. Abid Ali defends this off the front foot towards the on side.
An arm ball, on middle. Abid Ali pushes it to the off side off the back foot and wants a quick single but is sent back by his partner.
Tossed up on middle. Abid Ali defends this off the front foot.
Drifting away, outside off. Abdullah Shafique hangs back and brings his bat down. The ball goes off the outside edge to third man for a couple of runs.
Tossed up, outside off. Abdullah Shafique knocks it to mid-wicket.
Another quicker ball, on middle and leg. Abdullah Shafique drops it to short leg with soft hands.
Quicker, outside off. Abdullah Shafique pushes it towards covers.
Loopy ball, outside off. Abdullah Shafique drives it but finds the cover fielder.
Tossed up, down the leg side. Left alone.
Mehidy Hasan is brought into the attack. He replaces Ebadot Hossain.
Quicker on off. Abid Ali defends this off the back foot comfortably this time.
BEATEN! Wonderful drift and then a turn away! Tossed up, around middle and off. Abid Ali presses forward to defend but the ball turns away sharply to beat him all ends up.
Slower in the air, on leg. Abdullah Shafique nudges it to square leg for a single.
Shorter length, on off. Abid Ali punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
An arm ball this time on leg. Abid Ali looks to work it away but gets hit on the pads.
Tossed up on middle. Abid Ali defends this off the front foot towards the on side.
Sparying on the pads again, Abdullah Shafique clips it to mid-wicket in the gap for a couple.
Short ball again and this time Abid Ali pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Shorter length, on off. Abid Ali looks to pull it but the ball hurries a little on him as he gets it to mid on.
FOUR! Another very good shot by Abid Ali! Half-volley on pads, Abid Ali flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary. Nice timing on that one.
On a length, on off. Abid Ali blocks this right under his eyes.

FOUR! Gorgeous shot! Was a half-volley with width on offer, Abid Ali rides on the bounce, and plays a textbook cover-drive. He holds the pose in admiration! There is a kind of battle going on between Ebadot Hossain and Abid Ali and the latter is winning the battle with his bat.
A maiden! Loopy ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique is solid in his defence.

Drifting onto middle and leg, Abdullah Shafique watchfully blocks it out.
Loopy ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it out.

Overpitched ball, outside off. Abid Ali pushes it to the left of the bowler.
FOUR! Wow! Abid Ali replies with his bat. Short of a length, outside off. Abid Ali rides on top of the bounce and slashes it through point for a boundary.

Fuller in length, on off. Abid Ali drives it back to the bowler. Some aggression there by Ebadot Hossain as he collects the ball and throws it at the striker's end. That throws was absolutely needless as Abid Ali was inside the crease. Maybe just trying to get under batsman's skin.
Length ball, going down the leg side. Abid Ali leaves it alone.
On a good length, outside off. Abid Ali eases it towards covers.
FOUR! Nicely played! ball, on middle. Abdullah Shafique gets down on one knee and sweeps it hard to deep square leg. There is no protection in the deep and the ball races away to the boundary.

Tossed up, on off. Abdullah Shafique presses forward and blocks it out.
On off, pushed to point.
Flatter ball, on middle. Blocked out.
Full and on off, pushed back to the bowler.

That just took off the surface! Ebadot Hossain bangs a short ball, on middle. The ball goes swinging down the leg side. Abid Ali ducks under it. Liton Das does well to moves to his left and grab the ball.
Fuller in length, on off. Abid Ali drives it back to the bowler who does well to stop it on the followthrough.
Length ball, on middle. Abid Ali tucks it on the leg side. He calls for a single but is sent back by Abdullah Shafique.

Length ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique stands tall and plays it to mid-wicket.

Drifted on the pads, ticked to fine leg for a single.

NOT OUT! Length ball, on leg. Abid Ali looks to flick but misses out on his glance. There was a sound there and Bangladesh appeal for a caught behind but the umpire is unmoved. Ebadot Hossain seems pretty confident and convinces Mominul Haque to go for the review. UltraEdge shows there is no bat involved. The ball brushed off the pads and carried through to the keeper. Perhaps that was the sound which interested the bowler to go for the review. The on-field decision stays and Bangladesh lose a review early on.
Bangladesh have taken a review for caught behind! The replay rolls in and it shows nothing on the the UltraEdge as the ball passes the bat. So the decision stays and Bangladesh lose their review.
Good-length ball, outside off. Abid Ali watches the ball closely and shoulders arms to that.
